Material Information Summary – G50 Corp Ltd (ASX: G50)

Announcement Type: Exploration Results

Key Highlights:

  • New discovery confirmed at Golconda Project (Arizona) with high-grade intercepts:
  • GRC22: 47.2m at 2.0g/t Au, 40.2g/t Ag, and 0.29% Zn (including 16.8m at 5.19g/t Au and 100.2g/t Ag).
  • GRC21: 77.7m at 0.76g/t Au and 11g/t Ag (including 7.6m at 5.5g/t Au).
  • GRC17: 97.5m at 0.27g/t Au and 4.8g/t Ag (including 9.1m at 0.8g/t Au and 9.7g/t Ag).
  • Gallium results: Broad, shallow intercepts (e.g., 216m at 18.4g/t Ga in GRC13, 209m at 17.7g/t Ga in GRC14).
  • Mineralisation remains open along strike and at depth.

Next Steps:

  • Balance of Phase 2 assay results expected in 4–6 weeks.
  • Planning underway for follow-up drilling to test extensions.

No material capital or timetable information identified.

Note: Gold equivalents calculated using $2,800/oz Au, $28/oz Ag, $2,866/t Zn, $1,984/t Pb, $9,259/t Cu.

Material Information Summary

Exploration Update Announcement

  • Lucy Creek 2 Prospect (Manganese & Base Metals):
  • Portable XRF results indicate high-grade manganese (up to 33.56% MnO in sample RCLCK001) and elevated Pb, Zn, Ag (e.g., 1,131 ppm Pb, 1,133 ppm Zn in samples).
  • Potential hydrothermal manganese system, analogous to Bootu Creek (historic resource: 32.5Mt @ 22.6% Mn).

  • Planned work: Airborne magnetic/radiometric survey, ground EM, follow-up sampling/drilling.

  • Oonagalabi’s Bomb Diggity Prospect (Au-Bi-Cu-Zn):

  • Previous drilling intercept: 15m @ 0.45 g/t Au, 0.17% Bi, 0.35% Cu (OGRC002).
  • Upcoming diamond drillhole (partly NT Govt-funded) to test deep magnetic/gravity anomalies.

Key Implications for Traders/Investors:

  1. Exploration Upside: Confirmed high-grade Mn and base metals at Lucy Creek 2; potential for scalable resource.
  2. Catalysts: Near-term assay results (4–6 weeks), geophysical surveys, and drilling plans.
  3. Risks: Preliminary pXRF results require lab validation; no JORC Resource yet.

No capital raising, financials, or material corporate updates detected.

Material Information Summary (Corporate Presentation - ASX:GLA)

Investment Highlights

  • Uranium Exploration Focus: Targeting sandstone-hosted uranium deposits in Tanzania’s Selous Basin (Karoo Supergroup).
  • Key Project (Mkuju):
  • Contains Likuyu North deposit (JORC MRE: 4.6Mlb U₃O₈ at 267ppm, 100ppm cut-off).
  • ISR potential: Study confirms suitability for low-cost in-situ recovery (ISR) mining.
  • Mtonya-SWC corridor: High-grade intersections (e.g., 3.8m @ 2,458ppm eU₃O₈ at SWC).
  • Foxy Project: Untested uranium mineralization (2008 drill results: 6m @ 213ppm U₃O₈).
  • Eland Project: Early-stage Nb-Ta-U syenite target (44m @ 174ppm U₃O₈, 953ppm Nb₂O₅ via channel sampling).

Exploration Strategy

  • Prioritize Likuyu North expansion and Mtonya-SWC roll-front targets.
  • Planned low-cost drilling to test high-priority zones (e.g., SWC "nose" target, Likuyu South redox front).

Risks/Catalysts

  • Foreign estimates (Mtonya): Non-JORC inferred resource of 1.9Mlb U₃O₈ (293ppm, 100ppm cut-off) – requires further validation.
  • Uranium price leverage: Presentation highlights rising uranium market (spot price >USD70/lb).

No material financials or capital-raising details disclosed.
